{
  "bead_id": "B-4ff537b6",
  "title": "Skip git commit in _git_commit_bead when nothing is staged",
  "agent_type": "developer",
  "description": "In storage.py:_git_commit_bead(), git add is always followed by git commit unconditionally. When the bead JSON has not changed since the last commit (e.g. the feature root/epic bead being re-saved with identical content), git add stages nothing and git commit exits with code 1. This fires a logger.warning and appends a spurious git_commit_failed event to the bead's execution history on every occurrence, cluttering both the scheduler output and the bead audit trail.\n\nFix: after git add, run 'git diff --cached --quiet' and return early if the exit code is 0 (nothing staged), skipping the git commit entirely. Only attempt git commit when there are actually staged changes.\n\nThe change is in _git_commit_bead() in src/agent_takt/storage.py, between the git add and git commit subprocess calls.",
  "status": "in_progress",
  "bead_type": "task",
  "parent_id": null,
